Olalekan Adetayo, Abuja The Federal Government on Thursday said it has no plan to shut down the internet or social media.
It said it would only work with stakeholders to regulate social media. The Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed, said this at a press conference in Abuja. Mohammed observed that social media was used wrongly to cause mayhem in the aftermath of the #EndSARS protest. Details laterâ€¦